# ACT 4 (Bad)
[background arg="res://Art/Backgrounds/mayas_room.png" fade="0.7"]
The room is dimly lit. A desk lamp casts a warm glow over a cluttered study table.
Open textbooks. Printed reviewers. Half-finished thesis notes. Sticky notes cover the edges of Maya's laptop.
The wall calendar hangs nearby.
Almost every day has been crossed out.
The end of the term is only a few days away.
Maya sits at her desk, staring blankly at her laptop.
The cursor blinks.
Waiting.
She doesn't type a single word.
She rubs her tired eyes.
Her phone lights up.
A notification from the class group chat.
"MATE:"Guys, thesis progress update tomorrow.""   (Class)
Another message follows.
"MATE 2:"Pakisend na rin ng revisions before 10 PM.""   (Class)
Maya locks her phone without replying.
She leans back in her chair.
Letting out a long, exhausted sigh.
join Maya (neutral) leftmost [animation="Instant In"]
update Maya (soft)
Maya: Hay...
She glances at the calendar.
Then at the mountain of schoolwork covering her desk.
Another sigh escapes.
Her eyes slowly drift toward the ceiling.
Silence.
For the first time in days...
She allows herself to stop working.
Her thoughts begin to wander.
leave Maya [animation="Instant Out"]
[background arg="res://Art/Backgrounds/classroom.png" fade="0.7"]
The first day of the semester.
The professor stands at the front of the room.
join Professor (default) leftmost [animation="Instant In"]
Professor: "What are your future dreams and goals?"
The words echo.
Maya remembers standing in front of the class.
Frozen.
Unable to answer.
join Maya (neutral) leftmost [animation="Instant In"]
update Maya (soft)
Maya: "I haven't really thought about it yet."
The memory lingers.
Then fades.
leave Professor [animation="Instant Out"]
leave Maya [animation="Instant Out"]
[background arg="res://Art/Backgrounds/mayas_room.png" fade="0.7"]
Maya quietly stares at the blank wall.
A bitter smile forms.
Then disappears.
join Maya (neutral) leftmost [animation="Instant In"]
update Maya (soft)
Maya: Maybe...
update Maya (soft)
Maya: I did know.
Pause.
update Maya (soft)
Maya: I just didn't want to admit it.
She slowly looks around her room.
update Maya (soft)
Maya: Engineering books.
update Maya (soft)
Maya: Programming reviewers.
update Maya (soft)
Maya: Circuit diagrams pinned above her desk.
update Maya (soft)
Maya: Everything she had spent years convincing herself she wanted.
She closes her eyes.
update Maya (soft)
Maya: This...
update Maya (soft)
Maya: isn't me.
[signal arg="emphasis"]
Her voice cracks ever so slightly.
update Maya (sobbing)
Maya: This isn't the course I wanted.
The realization hangs in the silence.
update Maya (soft)
Maya: Not dramatic.
update Maya (soft)
Maya: Just honest.
Maya lowers her head.
A tear slips down her cheek.
She wipes it away before another can fall.
Her eyes drift toward the bottom shelf of her bookshelf.
Partially hidden beneath a stack of old folders..
A worn sketchbook.
Dust has begun collecting along its edges.
Maya stares at it.
She hesitates.
Then slowly reaches for it.
She brushes away the dust.
Running her fingers across the faded cover.
She opens it.
Inside are old drawings.
Landscapes.
Portraits.
Character sketches.
Small doodles in the margins.
She quietly smiles.
A real one.
The first genuine smile she's had in a long time.
She flips through another page.
Then another.
Finally...
She reaches for a pencil lying forgotten inside the sketchbook.
She hesitates.
Then begins to draw.
The graphite glides across the paper.
Gentle.
Effortless.
Time quietly passes.
The only sounds are the soft scratching of pencil against paper and the ticking of the clock.
Maya's tense shoulders slowly begin to relax.
Her breathing steadies.
For the first time in months...
She isn't thinking about grades.
Deadlines.
Expectations.
Or disappointing anyone.
She's simply..
Drawing.
A peaceful silence fills the room.
Unfamiliar.
But comforting.
She leans back to admire the unfinished sketch.
A small laugh escapes her.
update Maya (glad)
Maya: Mahaba pa pala...
hindi ko pa nakakalimutan.
She continues adding a few more lines.
Then...
Her eyes wander toward her laptop.
The unfinished thesis document remains open.
Beside it...
A printed checklist.
“Thesis Defense”
“Final Requirements”
“Graduation Clearance”
Her smile slowly fades.
Reality settles back into the room.
The peace she found lasts only a moment.
Maya gently closes the sketchbook.
Holding it against her chest.
She lowers her head.
update Maya (soft)
Maya: Ang saya sana...
update Maya (soft)
Maya: kung ganito na lang.
A long silence.
She carefully places the sketchbook inside her desk drawer.
Not throwing it away.
Not displaying it.
Simply...
Hiding it once again.
She takes one last deep breath.
Then pulls her laptop closer.
Her fingers return to the keyboard.
The cursor continues blinking.
Waiting.
leave Maya [animation="Instant Out"]
