The bright afternoon sun shines over a crowded school campus.
Children run through the gates, laughing as parents wait outside.
A Young Jennifer, around ten years old, walks out carrying a worn backpack and a rolled-up certificate.
She smiles to herself.
Excited.
Proud.
She scans the crowd.
Parents hug their children.
Some take photos.
Others congratulate them.
Jennifer keeps looking.
Waiting.
Her smile slowly fades.
No one comes.
She looks down at the certificate in her hands.
Across the school gate...
She notices her mother rushing toward her.
Still wearing her work uniform.
Hair slightly messy.
Clearly exhausted.
"JENNIFER!"   (Jennifer's mother)
"Pasensya ka na, anak."   (Jennifer's mother)
"Na-late si Mama."   (Jennifer's mother)
Young Jennifer quickly shakes her head.
"Okay lang po."   (young Jennifer)
Her mother smiles apologetically.
She kneels and gently brushes Jennifer's hair behind her ear.
"Congratulations."   (Ethan's mother)
"Alam kong pinaghirapan mo 'yan."   (Ethan's mother)
She looks at the certificate.
Her smile slowly fades.
"Anak..."   (Ethan's mother)
"Kung pwede lang..."   (Ethan's mother)
"Sana mas marami pa akong oras para sa'yo."   (Ethan's mother)
Young Jennifer smiles.
Trying to comfort her instead.
"Okay lang po, Ma."   (young Jennifer)
"Paglaki ko..."   (young Jennifer)
"Ako naman."   (young Jennifer)
"Ako mag-aalaga sa inyo."   (young Jennifer)
Her mother hugs her tightly.
Jennifer quietly hugs back.
