Jennifer studies.
Jennifer works.
Jennifer graduates.
Her mother proudly watches from the audience.
Jennifer holds her diploma tightly.
[signal arg="emphasis"]
Tears well in her eyes.
Not because she finished.
Because she finally kept her promise.
[background arg="res://Art/Backgrounds/campus_courtyard.png" fade="0.7"]
Years later.
Jennifer and a younger Ricardo walk across campus.
Both wearing company IDs.
Recently employed.
Laughing together.
join Ricardo (neutral) leftmost [animation="Instant In"]
update Ricardo (glad)
Ricardo: Alam mo...
update Ricardo (glad)
Ricardo: Ngayon lang nagsi-sink in.
update Ricardo (glad)
Ricardo: Graduate na talaga tayo.
"Oo nga."   (young Jennifer)
"Ang bilis."   (young Jennifer)
Ricardo smiles.
update Ricardo (glad)
Ricardo: Ano'ng una mong bibilhin sa first salary mo?
Jennifer doesn't hesitate.
"Para kay Mama."   (young Jennifer)
Ricardo chuckles.
update Ricardo (glad)
Ricardo: Syempre.
Jennifer smiles warmly.
leave Ricardo [animation="Instant Out"]
[background arg="res://Mocks/Novel UI/image 3.png" fade="0.7"]
A much younger Maya, around six years old, sits at the dining table.
Crayons scattered everywhere.
Sheets of paper covered in colorful drawings.
"Mama!"   (young Maya)
"Tingnan mo!"   (young Maya)
Jennifer walks over.
She kneels beside Maya.
"Wow..."   (young Jennifer)
"Ikaw gumawa nito?"   (young Jennifer)
Young Maya nods excitedly.
"Opo!"   (young Maya)
"Gusto ko maging artist paglaki!"   (young Maya)
Jennifer laughs softly.
She gently pinches Maya's cheek.
"Ang ganda naman."   (young Jennifer)
She places the drawing on the refrigerator.
"Draw ka lang nang draw, ha?"   (young Jennifer)
Young Maya beams.
[background arg="res://Mocks/Novel UI/image 3.png" fade="0.7"]
The drawings on the refrigerator increase.
Maya proudly shows Jennifer every new sketch.
Jennifer keeps every single one in a folder.
Maya wins a school art contest.
Jennifer cheers the loudest.
Ricardo takes photos.
The family celebrates together.
[background arg="res://Mocks/Novel UI/image 3.png" fade="0.7"]
Maya is now in high school.
College brochures cover the dining table.
Jennifer flips through them carefully.
"Ma..."   (young Maya)
"Paano kung Fine Arts?"   (young Maya)
Jennifer pauses.
She looks at Maya.
Then at the brochure.
A long silence.
"Anak..."   (young Jennifer)
"Magaling ka talaga mag-drawing."   (young Jennifer)
"Pero..."   (young Jennifer)
"Mahirap ang buhay ng artist."   (young Jennifer)
Maya quietly listens.
"Gusto ko..."   (young Jennifer)
"Mas sigurado ang future mo."   (young Jennifer)
"Ayokong maranasan mo 'yung hirap na naranasan ko."   (young Jennifer)
Maya slowly nods.
She doesn't argue.
She simply folds the Fine Arts brochure.
And places it underneath the others.
Jennifer notices.
But says nothing.
[background arg="res://Art/Backgrounds/mayas_room.png" fade="0.7"]
Maya studies Computer Science.
Engineering books replace sketchpads.
The refrigerator no longer displays new drawings.
The folder of childhood artwork slowly gathers dust.
Jennifer passes Maya's room.
She smiles proudly.
Believing everything is going according to plan.
She never notices...
The sketchbook tucked away inside the drawer.
Or the way Maya quietly stares at it before turning back to her engineering books.
[background arg="res://Mocks/Novel UI/image 3.png" fade="0.7"]
The memories begin overlapping.
Young Maya smiling with crayons.
Young Maya winning art contests.
Young Maya saying...
"Gusto ko maging artist paglaki."   (young Maya)
[signal arg="emphasis"]
Jennifer freezes.
The words echo.
Again.
And again.
Her eyes slowly widen.
join Jennifer (neutral) leftmost [animation="Instant In"]
update Jennifer (glad)
Jennifer: ...
update Jennifer (teary)
Jennifer: Hindi niya pala nakalimutan.
